Pre-Game Insights: Egypt and Tanzania will play in a friendly match in Egypt on January 7, 2024.
Adel Amrouche, the Taifa Stars head coach, is expected to use the camp in Egypt to prepare his team well ahead of the AFCON campaign.
Egypt, Ghana, Cape Verde, and Mozambique are a part of Group B in AFCON 2023.
Tanzania is placed in Group F alongside Morocco, DR Congo, and Zambia.
Mohamed Salah will be the main player for Egypt, with high expectations from Liverpool’s forward.
Mbwana Samatta, PAOK striker, has scored 17 goals in 36 matches for Tanzania and will aim to add a goal or two against Egypt.
Egypt have won the last three meetings between these two teams.
Tanzania are unbeaten in the last seven away matches.
Egypt coach Rui Vitoria will test his players ahead of the AFCON 2023 and give them maximum game time.
Predicted lineup for Egypt: El Shenawi, Hamdy, Abdelmonem, Gabr, Hany, Elneny, Fahi, Zizo, Trezeguet, Moustafe, Salah.
Predicted lineup for Tanzania: Kawawa, Miroshi, Hamad, Mwamnyeto, Job, Bajan, Mnoga, Salum, M’Mombwa, Samatta, Msuva.
Egypt are the favourites to win the match in front of the home crowd.
